    return df.drop(variables_list, axis=1)

#For missing values
def deal_with_missing_values(df):
    return df.replace('(null)', np.nan)
In [ ]:
#Y/N flags to bool
def convert_flags_to_boolean(df):
    binary_map_dict = {'Y': 1, 'N': 0, np.nan: 0, 'I':1, 'S':1, 'V':1}
    # binary_map_dict = {'Y': 1, 'N': 0, 'I': 1, 'S': 1, 'V': 1, 'True': 1, 'False': 0}

    # carrying out this operation for flags
    for col in df.columns:
        if 'FLAG' in col:
            df[col] = list(map(lambda x: binary_map_dict[x], df[col]))
    return df
In [ ]:
#Convert categorical variables to one-hot-encoding
def make_one_hot(df, var):
    one_hot = pd.get_dummies(df[var], drop_first=True)
    df = df.drop(var,axis = 1)
    df = df.join(one_hot)
    return df

# For height: converting feet to inches
def replace_feet_inches(h):
    try:
        height = str(h).split('.')
        return int(height[0])*12 + int(height[1])
    except:
        return h

def data_cleaning_pipeline(df):
    unnecessary_variables = ['STOP_LOCATION_PREMISES_NAME', 'STOP_FRISK_ID', 'YEAR2', 'RECORD_STATUS_CODE']

    #Drop Variables
    df = drop_unnecessary_variables(df, unnecessary_variables)

    #Mmissing values
    df = deal_with_missing_values(df)

    #Y/N flags to booleans and doing the same for gender
    df = convert_flags_to_boolean(df)
    df = replace_with_map(df, 'SUSPECT_SEX', {'MALE': 1, 'FEMALE': 0, np.nan: np.nan})

    #MONTH2 name to num
    month_list = 'January February March April May June July August September October November December'.split()
    month_dict = {month:i for i, month in enumerate(month_list)}
    df = replace_with_map(df, 'MONTH2', month_dict)

    #DAY2 name to num
    day_list = 'Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Saturday Sunday'.split()
    day_dict = {month:i for i, month in enumerate(day_list)}
    df = replace_with_map(df, 'DAY2', day_dict)

    stop_dict = {'Based on C/W on Scene': 0, 'Based on Radio Run': 1, 'Based on Self Initiated': 2}
    df = replace_with_map(df, 'STOP_WAS_INITIATED', stop_dict)

    #Specific variable transformations
    df = specific_variable_transformations(df)

    #Categorical variables to one-hot
    df = make_one_hot(df, 'SUSPECT_RACE_DESCRIPTION')
    df = make_one_hot(df, 'SUSPECTED_CRIME_DESCRIPTION')
    df = make_one_hot(df, 'STOP_LOCATION_BORO_NAME')

    print('Cleaned dataframe shape: {}'.format(df.shape))
    return df

#Visualisation of Top K Features
def top_k_features(features, feature_importances, k=10):
    indices = np.argsort(feature_importances)[-k:]
    return indices, features[indices], feature_importances[indices]

def get_X_y(df, drop_cols=[]):
    df['SUSPECT_SEX'] = df['SUSPECT_SEX'].replace("Unknown", 1)
    model_df = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'uint8', 'float64']).dropna(axis=0)
    y = np.array(model_df['SUSPECT_ARRESTED_FLAG'])
    X = model_df[model_df.columns.difference(['SUSPECT_ARRESTED_FLAG', 'SEARCH_BASIS_INCIDENTAL_TO_ARREST_FLAG'])]
    X = X[X.columns.difference(drop_cols)]
    return X, y

def plot_cm(y_true, y_pred, classes,name,ax,cmap=plt.cm.Blues):

    title = 'Confusion Matrix for {}'.format(name)
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    ax.grid(False)
    im = ax.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    ax.set(xticks=np.arange(cm.shape[1]),yticks=np.arange(cm.shape[0]),
           xticklabels=classes, yticklabels=classes)
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=20)
    ax.set_xlabel('Predicted label', fontsize=15)
    ax.set_ylabel('True label', fontsize=15)

    # Rotate the tick labels and set their alignment.
    plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right", rotation_mode="anchor", fontsize=10)

    # Loop over data dimensions and create text annotations.
    fmt = 'd'
    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i in range(cm.shape[0]):
        for j in range(cm.shape[1]):
            ax.text(j, i, format(cm[i, j], fmt),ha="center", va="center",
                    color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black", fontsize=20)
    return ax
In [ ]:
def plot_feature_imp(X_tr, model, name, ax, k=10):
    indices, features, importances = top_k_features(X_tr.columns, model.feature_importances_, k)

    ax.barh(range(len(indices)), importances, color='b', align='center')
    ax.set_yticks(range(len(indices)))
    ax.set_yticklabels(features)
    ax.set_xlabel('Relative Importance', fontsize=15)
    ax.set_title('Top {} Features of {}'.format(k, name), fontsize=20)
    return ax

import pandas as pd

if 'clean_sqf_df' in locals() or 'clean_sqf_df' in globals():
    # Identify columns with boolean-like values (stored as strings)
    bool_cols = clean_sqf_df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns

    # Filter only columns that contain 'True' or 'False' as string values
    bool_cols = [col for col in bool_cols if clean_sqf_df[col].isin(['True', 'False']).any()]

    # Convert 'True' to 1 and 'False' to 0
    clean_sqf_df[bool_cols] = clean_sqf_df[bool_cols].replace({'True': 1, 'False': 0}).astype(int)

    # Display the first few rows to verify changes
    print(clean_sqf_df.head())

    # Optionally save the cleaned dataset
    clean_sqf_df.to_csv("cleaned_sqf_data.csv", index=False)
    print("Updated dataset saved as 'cleaned_sqf_data.csv'.")

else:
    print("Error: The dataset (clean_sqf_df) is not loaded. Ensure it is assigned correctly.")

def groupRates(test_predictions, sensitive, y_test):
    # True positives for z=1 and z=0
    # d[1] = sensitive attribute; d[2] = label
    TP_z1 = sum([y and p for (p,x,y) in zip(test_predictions,sensitive,y_test) if x])
    FN_z1 = sum([y and not p for (p,x,y) in zip(test_predictions,sensitive,y_test) if x])
    TP_z0 = sum([y and p for (p,x,y) in zip(test_predictions,sensitive,y_test) if not x])
    FN_z0 = sum([y and not p for (p,x,y) in zip(test_predictions,sensitive,y_test) if not x])
    # Convert to rates
    TPR1 = 0
    TPR0 = 0
    if TP_z1 > 0:
        TPR1 = TP_z1 / (TP_z1 + FN_z1)
    if TP_z0 > 0:
        TPR0 = TP_z0 / (TP_z0 + FN_z0)
    return TPR1, TPR0

def sampling(X_data, y_data, df_data):
    data_col = df_data['SUSPECT_SEX'].values.tolist()

    male_1 = [(x, y, d) for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, data_col) if y == 1 and d == 1.0]
    male_0 = [(x, y, d) for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, data_col) if y == 0 and d == 1.0]
    female_1 = [(x, y, d) for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, data_col) if y == 1 and d == 0.0]
    female_0 = [(x, y, d) for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, data_col) if y == 0 and d == 0.0]

    len_list = sorted([len(male_1), len(male_0), len(female_1), len(female_0)])

    sample_num = len_list[-1]
    list_dict = {
        (0, 0): female_0,
        (0, 1): female_1,
        (1, 0): male_0,
        (1, 1): male_1
    }

    new_data = []
    for s in [0, 1]:
        for c in [0, 1]:
            temp_list = list_dict[(s, c)]
            for _ in range(sample_num):
                temp_data = random.choice(temp_list)
                new_data.append(temp_data)

    random.shuffle(new_data)
    new_X = [x for x,_,_ in new_data]
    new_y = [y for _,y,_ in new_data]
    new_d = [d for _,_,d in new_data]
    return new_X, new_y, new_d

def sampling(X_data, y_data, df_data):
    white_data = df_data['WHITE'].tolist()
    white_hispanic = df_data['WHITE HISPANIC'].tolist()
    black = df_data['BLACK'].tolist()
    black_hispanic = df_data['BLACK HISPANIC'].tolist()
    asian_pacific = df_data['ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER'].tolist()

    white_1 = [(x, y, "WHITE") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, white_data) if y == 1 and d]
    white_0 = [(x, y, "WHITE") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, white_data) if y == 0 and d]
    white_hispanic_1 = [(x, y, "WHITE HISPANIC") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, white_hispanic) if y == 1 and d]
    white_hispanic_0 = [(x, y, "WHITE HISPANIC") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, white_hispanic) if y == 0 and d]
    black_1 = [(x, y, "BLACK") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, black) if y == 1 and d]
    black_0 = [(x, y, "BLACK") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, black) if y == 0 and d]
    black_hispanic_1 = [(x, y, "BLACK HISPANIC") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, black_hispanic) if y == 1 and d]
    black_hispanic_0 = [(x, y, "BLACK HISPANIC") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, black_hispanic) if y == 0 and d]
    asian_pacific_1 = [(x, y, "ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, asian_pacific) if y == 1 and d]
    asian_pacific_0 = [(x, y, "ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER") for (x, y, d) in zip(X_data, y_data, asian_pacific) if y == 0 and d]

    len_list = sorted([len(white_1), len(white_0), len(white_hispanic_1), len(white_hispanic_1),
    len(white_hispanic_0), len(black_1), len(black_0), len(black_hispanic_1), len(black_hispanic_0),
    len(asian_pacific_1), len(asian_pacific_0)])

    sample_num = (len_list[4] + len_list[5]) // 2
    list_dict = {
        ("WHITE", 0): white_0,
        ("WHITE", 1): white_1,
        ("WHITE HISPANIC", 0): white_hispanic_0,
        ("WHITE HISPANIC", 1): white_hispanic_1,
        ("BLACK", 0): black_0,
        ("BLACK", 1): black_1,
        ("BLACK HISPANIC", 0): black_hispanic_0,
        ("BLACK HISPANIC", 1): black_hispanic_1,
        ("ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER", 0): asian_pacific_0,
        ("ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER", 1): asian_pacific_1,
    }

    new_data = []
    for s in ["WHITE", "WHITE HISPANIC", "BLACK", "BLACK HISPANIC", "ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER"]:
        for c in [0, 1]:
            temp_list = list_dict[(s, c)]
            for _ in range(sample_num):
                temp_data = random.choice(temp_list)
                new_data.append(temp_data)

    random.shuffle(new_data)
    new_X = [x for x,_,_ in new_data]
    new_y = [y for _,y,_ in new_data]
    new_d = [d for _,_,d in new_data]
    return new_X, new_y, new_d

Code: Can you apply post-processing interventions to achieve desired fairness outcomes?¶

In [ ]:
# Strong Equalized Odds
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression

def TPR(y_true, y_pred):
    TP = np.sum((y_true == 1) & (y_pred == 1))
    FN = np.sum((y_true == 1) & (y_pred == 0))
    return TP / (TP + FN) if (TP + FN) > 0 else 0

def FPR(y_true, y_pred):
    FP = np.sum((y_true == 0) & (y_pred == 1))
    TN = np.sum((y_true == 0) & (y_pred == 0))
    return FP / (FP + TN) if (FP + TN) > 0 else 0

def balanced_accuracy(y_true, y_pred):
    tpr = TPR(y_true, y_pred)
    fpr = FPR(y_true, y_pred)
    return (tpr + (1 - fpr)) / 2

def compute_dynamic_weights(tpr_diff, fpr_diff):
    weight_factor = 1 / (tpr_diff + fpr_diff + 1e-6)
    return weight_factor

# for equalized odds
def equalize_odds_postprocessing(X_test, y_test, model, sensitive_attributes):
    thresholds = {}
    weights = {}

    test_probs = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

    # Compute balanced accuracy of the original model
    normal_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, (test_probs >= 0.5).astype(int))
    print("Logistic Regression Model Balanced Accuracy:", normal_acc)

    # to find optimal per-group thresholds
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        mask_1 = (X_test[attr] == 1)  # Group where attr = 1
        mask_0 = (X_test[attr] == 0)  # Group where attr = 0

        best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = 0.5, 0.5
        min_tpr_diff = float("inf")
        min_fpr_diff = float("inf")
        min_acc = 0

        for thresh_1 in np.linspace(0.1, 0.9, 100):
            for thresh_0 in np.linspace(0.1, 0.9, 100):

                y_pred_testing = np.zeros_like(y_test)

                # Apply per-group thresholds
                y_pred_testing[mask_1] = (test_probs[mask_1] >= thresh_1).astype(int)
                y_pred_testing[mask_0] = (test_probs[mask_0] >= thresh_0).astype(int)

                # Compute TPR and FPR for each group
                tpr_1, fpr_1 = TPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_testing[mask_1]), FPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_testing[mask_1])
                tpr_0, fpr_0 = TPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_testing[mask_0]), FPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_testing[mask_0])

                # Compute difference
                tpr_diff = abs(tpr_1 - tpr_0)
                fpr_diff = abs(fpr_1 - fpr_0)

                # Compute current test balanced accuracy for the current threshold
                current_test_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, y_pred_testing)

                # Check if this threshold improves fairness and maintains accuracy
                if current_test_acc > min_acc and tpr_diff < min_tpr_diff and fpr_diff < min_fpr_diff:
                    best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = thresh_1, thresh_0
                    min_tpr_diff = tpr_diff
                    min_fpr_diff = fpr_diff
                    min_acc = current_test_acc

        thresholds[attr] = (best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0)
        print(f"Optimal thresholds for {attr}: {best_thresh_1}, {best_thresh_0}")

    print("\nFinal Per-Group TPR & FPR Before Post-Processing:")
    y_preds = model.predict(X_test)
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        for group in [0, 1]:
            mask = (X_test[attr] == group)
            if np.sum(mask) > 0:
                tpr = TPR(y_test[mask], y_preds[mask])
                fpr = FPR(y_test[mask], y_preds[mask])
                print(f"TPR for {attr}={group}: {tpr}, FPR: {fpr}")


    # for final test predictions after post-processing
    y_pred_adjusted_list = []

    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        mask_0 = (X_test[attr] == 0)  # Group where attr = 0
        mask_1 = (X_test[attr] == 1)  # Group where attr = 1

        best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = thresholds[attr]

        y_pred_adjusted = np.zeros_like(y_test)
        y_pred_adjusted[mask_1] = (test_probs[mask_1] >= best_thresh_1).astype(int)
        y_pred_adjusted[mask_0] = (test_probs[mask_0] >= best_thresh_0).astype(int)
        y_pred_adjusted_list.append(y_pred_adjusted)

        # Compute TPR and FPR for group 0
        tpr_0 = TPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_adjusted[mask_0])
        fpr_0 = FPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_adjusted[mask_0])

        # Calculate TPR and FPR for group 1
        tpr_1 = TPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_adjusted[mask_1])
        fpr_1 = FPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_adjusted[mask_1])

        # Compute disparities between TPR and FPR of the two groups for dynamic weight calculation
        tpr_diff = abs(tpr_0 - tpr_1)
        fpr_diff = abs(fpr_0 - fpr_1)

        # Compute dynamic weights
        weight = compute_dynamic_weights(tpr_diff, fpr_diff)
        weights[attr] = weight

    # Normalize the weights
    weight_values = np.array(list(weights.values()))
    weight_values /= np.sum(weight_values)
    y_pred_adjusted_list = np.array(y_pred_adjusted_list)

    # Weighted Aggregation of final adjusted Predictions
    final_probs = np.average(y_pred_adjusted_list, axis=0, weights=weight_values)
    y_pred_final = (final_probs >= 0.5).astype(int)

    # Compute final accuracy
    final_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, y_pred_final)
    print("\nFinal Fair Model Balanced Accuracy:", final_acc)

    # Final TPR and FPR per group
    print("\nFinal Per-Group TPR & FPR After Post-Processing:")
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        for group in [0, 1]:
            mask = (X_test[attr] == group)
            if np.sum(mask) > 0:
                tpr = TPR(y_test[mask], y_pred_final[mask])
                fpr = FPR(y_test[mask], y_pred_final[mask])
                print(f"TPR for {attr}={group}: {tpr}, FPR: {fpr}")

    return final_acc, thresholds

sensitive_attributes = ["SUSPECT_SEX", "ASIAN / PACIFIC ISLANDER", "BLACK", "BLACK HISPANIC", "WHITE", "WHITE HISPANIC"]

# Train logistic regression model
model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)

print("\nFinal Fair Model Accuracy after post-processing:", final_acc)
print("Final Per-Group Thresholds:", final_thresholds)

# Weak Equalized Odds: Global Threshold that Minimizes Disparity
def equalize_global_threshold(X_train_fu, y_train_fu, X_test_fu, y_test_fu, accuracy_weight=0.5):
    best_thresh = 0.5
    min_disparity = float("inf")
    normal_acc = 0

    # Train logistic regression model for balanced accuracy
    model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=42)
    model.fit(X_train_fu, y_train_fu)
    test_probs = model.predict_proba(X_test_fu)[:, 1]

    normal_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test_fu, (test_probs >= 0.5).astype(int))
    print("Original Model Balanced Accuracy on Test Set:", normal_acc)

    # Search for the best single threshold based on testing data
    for thresh in np.linspace(0, 1, 100):
        y_pred_test = (test_probs >= thresh).astype(int)

        tpr_values, fpr_values = [], []

        for attr in sensitive_attributes:
            for group in [0, 1]:
                mask = (X_test_fu[attr] == group)
                if np.sum(mask) == 0:
                    continue

                tpr = TPR(y_test_fu[mask], y_pred_test[mask])
                fpr = FPR(y_test_fu[mask], y_pred_test[mask])

                tpr_values.append(tpr)
                fpr_values.append(fpr)

        # Compute disparities across groups
        if tpr_values and fpr_values:
            tpr_disparity = max(tpr_values) - min(tpr_values)
            fpr_disparity = max(fpr_values) - min(fpr_values)

            # Calculate balanced accuracy using current threshold
            y_preds_testing = (test_probs >= thresh).astype(int)
            test_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test_fu, y_preds_testing)

            accuracy_diff = abs(test_acc - normal_acc)

            max_disparity = max(tpr_disparity, fpr_disparity)

            # total_loss for balancing the tradeoff between model accuracy and fairness
            total_loss = (1 - accuracy_weight) * max_disparity + accuracy_weight * accuracy_diff

            if total_loss < min_disparity:
                best_thresh = thresh
                min_disparity = total_loss

    # Apply the best threshold to the test set
    y_preds_test = (test_probs >= best_thresh).astype(int)

    tpr_values_test, fpr_values_test = [], []
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        for group in [0, 1]:
            mask = (X_test_fu[attr] == group)

            tpr_test = TPR(y_test_fu[mask], y_preds_test[mask])
            fpr_test = FPR(y_test_fu[mask], y_preds_test[mask])

            tpr_values_test.append(tpr_test)
            fpr_values_test.append(fpr_test)

            print(f"Test - Attr: {attr}, Group: {group} -> TPR: {tpr_test}, FPR: {fpr_test}")

    tpr_disparity_test = max(tpr_values_test) - min(tpr_values_test)
    fpr_disparity_test = max(fpr_values_test) - min(fpr_values_test)

    accuracy = balanced_accuracy(y_test_fu, y_preds_test)

    return accuracy, best_thresh, tpr_disparity_test, fpr_disparity_test

import numpy as np
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

def apply_platt_scaling(model, X_train, y_train, X_test):
    """
    Returns the Calibrated predicted probabilities for the test set.
    """

    model_probs = model.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1]

    platt_scaling = LogisticRegression()
    platt_scaling.fit(model_probs.reshape(-1, 1), y_train)

    test_probs = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

    calibrated_probs = platt_scaling.predict_proba(test_probs.reshape(-1, 1))[:, 1]
    return calibrated_probs

def equalize_odds_with_platt_scaling(X_test, y_test, model, sensitive_attributes, normal_original_acc):

    test_probs = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    print("Raw Test Probabilities:", test_probs)

    calibrated_probs = apply_platt_scaling(model, X_train_fu, y_train_fu, X_test)
    print("Calibrated Test Probabilities after Platt Scaling:", calibrated_probs)

    thresholds = {}  # Store per-group thresholds
    weights = {}

    # Compute Logistic_Regression model balanced accuracy with calibrated probabilities
    normal_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, (calibrated_probs >= 0.5).astype(int))
    print("Original Model Accuracy after Platt Scaling:", normal_acc)
    min_acc = normal_acc - 5

    # Find optimal per-group thresholds
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        mask_1 = (X_test[attr] == 1)  # Group where attr = 1
        mask_0 = (X_test[attr] == 0)  # Group where attr = 0

        best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = 0.5, 0.5
        min_tpr_diff = float("inf")
        min_fpr_diff = float("inf")

        for thresh_1 in np.linspace(0.1, 0.9, 100):
            for thresh_0 in np.linspace(0.1, 0.9, 100):

                y_pred_testing = np.zeros_like(y_test)

                y_pred_testing[mask_1] = (calibrated_probs[mask_1] >= thresh_1).astype(int)
                y_pred_testing[mask_0] = (calibrated_probs[mask_0] >= thresh_0).astype(int)

                # TPR and FPR for each group
                tpr_1, fpr_1 = TPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_testing[mask_1]), FPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_testing[mask_1])
                tpr_0, fpr_0 = TPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_testing[mask_0]), FPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_testing[mask_0])

                tpr_diff = abs(tpr_1 - tpr_0)
                fpr_diff = abs(fpr_1 - fpr_0)

                current_test_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, y_pred_testing)

                # Check if the current threshold improves fairness and maintains accuracy
                if current_test_acc > min_acc and tpr_diff < min_tpr_diff and fpr_diff < min_fpr_diff:
                    best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = thresh_1, thresh_0
                    min_tpr_diff = tpr_diff
                    min_fpr_diff = fpr_diff

        thresholds[attr] = (best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0)
        print(f"Optimal thresholds for {attr}: {best_thresh_1}, {best_thresh_0}")

    # Applying the intervention of the test set to get better results
    y_pred_adjusted_list = []
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        mask_0 = (X_test[attr] == 0)  # Group 0
        mask_1 = (X_test[attr] == 1)  # Group 1

        best_thresh_1, best_thresh_0 = thresholds[attr]

        y_pred_adjusted = np.zeros_like(y_test)
        y_pred_adjusted[mask_1] = (calibrated_probs[mask_1] >= best_thresh_1).astype(int)
        y_pred_adjusted[mask_0] = (calibrated_probs[mask_0] >= best_thresh_0).astype(int)
        y_pred_adjusted_list.append(y_pred_adjusted)

        # Compute TPR and FPR for group 0
        tpr_0 = TPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_adjusted[mask_0])
        fpr_0 = FPR(y_test[mask_0], y_pred_adjusted[mask_0])

        # Calculate TPR and FPR for group 1
        tpr_1 = TPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_adjusted[mask_1])
        fpr_1 = FPR(y_test[mask_1], y_pred_adjusted[mask_1])

        # Compute disparities between TPR and FPR of the two groups
        tpr_diff = abs(tpr_0 - tpr_1)
        fpr_diff = abs(fpr_0 - fpr_1)

        # Compute dynamic weight based on disparities
        weight = compute_dynamic_weights(tpr_diff, fpr_diff)
        weights[attr] = weight

    # Normalize the weights
    weight_values = np.array(list(weights.values()))
    weight_values /= np.sum(weight_values)
    y_pred_adjusted_list = np.array(y_pred_adjusted_list)

    # Weighted Aggregation of Adjusted Predictions
    final_probs = np.average(y_pred_adjusted_list, axis=0, weights=weight_values)
    y_pred_final = (final_probs >= 0.5).astype(int)

    final_acc = balanced_accuracy(y_test, y_pred_final)
    print("\nFinal Fair Model Accuracy:", final_acc)

    print("\nFinal Per-Group TPR & FPR After Post-Processing:")
    for attr in sensitive_attributes:
        for group in [0, 1]:
            mask = (X_test[attr] == group)
            if np.sum(mask) > 0:
                tpr = TPR(y_test[mask], y_pred_final[mask])
                fpr = FPR(y_test[mask], y_pred_final[mask])
                print(f"TPR for {attr}={group}: {tpr}, FPR: {fpr}")

    return final_acc, thresholds

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

def preferential_sampling_all(X, y, sensitive_attrs):
    """
    Implements Preferential Sampling for multiple sensitive attributes simultaneously.

    Parameters:
        X (pd.DataFrame): Feature matrix.
        y (pd.Series): Target variable (binary: 0/1).
        sensitive_attrs (list): List of sensitive attributes to consider.

    Returns:
        X_resampled (pd.DataFrame): Resampled feature matrix.
        y_resampled (pd.Series): Resampled target variable.
    """
    df = X.copy()
    df["label"] = y

    # Create a single combined sensitive attribute by concatenating all sensitive attributes
    df["sensitive_combined"] = df[sensitive_attrs].astype(str).agg("_".join, axis=1)

    # Step 1-2: Compute W(s,c) - Weight Calculation
    group_sizes = df.groupby(["sensitive_combined", "label"]).size()
    total_size = len(df)
    W = {}

    for (s, c), count in group_sizes.items():
        W[(s, c)] = (df[df["sensitive_combined"] == s].shape[0] * df[df["label"] == c].shape[0]) / (total_size * count)

    # Step 3: Learn a ranker R (Random Forest as a ranking model)
    ranker = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=5, random_state=0)
    ranker.fit(X, y)
    scores = ranker.predict_proba(X)[:, 1]

    df["rank_score"] = scores

    # Step 4: Create DPS - Preferential Sampling Set
    DPS = pd.DataFrame(columns=df.columns)

    for (s, c) in W:
        subset = df[(df["sensitive_combined"] == s) & (df["label"] == c)]

        if c == 1:  # Positive Class
            sorted_subset = subset.sort_values(by="rank_score", ascending=False)  # Higher-ranked first
        else:  # Negative Class
            sorted_subset = subset.sort_values(by="rank_score", ascending=True)  # Lower-ranked first

        num_full_copies = int(W[(s, c)])
        fractional_part = W[(s, c)] - num_full_copies

        # Step 5-6: Add full copies
        for _ in range(num_full_copies):
            DPS = pd.concat([DPS, sorted_subset], ignore_index=True)

        # Step 7-8: Add fractionally sampled copies
        num_fractional = int(fractional_part * len(subset))
        DPS = pd.concat([DPS, sorted_subset.head(num_fractional)], ignore_index=True)

    # Step 9-14: Return Resampled Dataset
    X_resampled = DPS.drop(columns=["label", "sensitive_combined", "rank_score"])
    y_resampled = DPS["label"].astype(int)

    return X_resampled, y_resampled

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score

def compute_tpr_fpr_accuracy(y_true, y_pred, sensitive_attr, X_test):
    """
    Computes TPR, FPR, and Accuracy for privileged vs disadvantaged groups.

    Parameters:
        y_true (array): True labels.
        y_pred (array): Predicted labels.
        sensitive_attr (str): Sensitive attribute name.
        X_test (DataFrame): Test dataset.

    Returns:
        dict: Metrics including TPR, FPR, and Accuracy.
    """
    privileged_idx = X_test[sensitive_attr] == 1  # Privileged group
    disadvantaged_idx = X_test[sensitive_attr] == 0  # Disadvantaged group

    # Ensure at least some samples exist for both groups
    if privileged_idx.sum() == 0 or disadvantaged_idx.sum() == 0:
        return {
            "TPR (Privileged)": None, "FPR (Privileged)": None,
            "TPR (Disadvantaged)": None, "FPR (Disadvantaged)": None,
            "Overall Accuracy": None
        }

    # Compute Confusion Matrices
    tn_p, fp_p, fn_p, tp_p = confusion_matrix(y_true[privileged_idx], y_pred[privileged_idx]).ravel()
    tn_d, fp_d, fn_d, tp_d = confusion_matrix(y_true[disadvantaged_idx], y_pred[disadvantaged_idx]).ravel()

    # Compute TPR & FPR
    TPR_privileged = tp_p / (tp_p + fn_p) if (tp_p + fn_p) > 0 else 0
    FPR_privileged = fp_p / (fp_p + tn_p) if (fp_p + tn_p) > 0 else 0
    TPR_disadvantaged = tp_d / (tp_d + fn_d) if (tp_d + fn_d) > 0 else 0
    FPR_disadvantaged = fp_d / (fp_d + tn_d) if (fp_d + tn_d) > 0 else 0

    # Compute Overall Accuracy
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred) * 100  # Convert to percentage

    return {
        "TPR (Privileged)": round(TPR_privileged, 4),
        "FPR (Privileged)": round(FPR_privileged, 4),
        "TPR (Disadvantaged)": round(TPR_disadvantaged, 4),
        "FPR (Disadvantaged)": round(FPR_disadvantaged, 4),
        "Overall Accuracy": round(accuracy, 2)
    }

import pandas as pd

# Standardize Model Names for Merging
model_name_map = {
    "Preferential Sampling - Random Forest": "Random Forest (Full)",
    "Preferential Sampling - AdaBoost": "AdaBoost (Full)",
    "Preferential Sampling - Logistic Regression": "Logistic Regression (Full)"
}
fairness_ps_df["Model"] = fairness_ps_df["Model"].replace(model_name_map)

# List of models
models = ["Random Forest (Full)", "AdaBoost (Full)", "Logistic Regression (Full)"]

# Dictionary to store separate DataFrames for each model
model_dataframes = {}

for model in models:
    # Filter Before & After PS Data
    df_before = fairness_df[fairness_df["Model"] == model]
    df_after = fairness_ps_df[fairness_ps_df["Model"] == model]

    # Merge Data
    model_comparison_df = pd.merge(
        df_before, df_after,
        on=["Model", "Sensitive Attribute"], how="inner", suffixes=("_Before", "_After")
    )

    # Store in dictionary
    model_dataframes[model] = model_comparison_df

# Assign separate DataFrames for each model
rf_fairness_comparison_df = model_dataframes["Random Forest (Full)"]
ab_fairness_comparison_df = model_dataframes["AdaBoost (Full)"]
lr_fairness_comparison_df = model_dataframes["Logistic Regression (Full)"]

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Function to plot fairness metric comparisons
def plot_fairness_metrics(df, model_name):
    sensitive_attrs = df["Sensitive Attribute"]
    x = np.arange(len(sensitive_attrs))  # Label positions

    # Metrics
    metrics = ["TPR (Privileged)", "FPR (Privileged)", "TPR (Disadvantaged)", "FPR (Disadvantaged)", "Overall Accuracy"]

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20, 5), sharey=False)

    for i, metric in enumerate(metrics):
        before_values = df[f"{metric}_Before"]
        after_values = df[f"{metric}_After"]

        ax = axes[i]
        ax.bar(x - 0.2, before_values, width=0.4, label="Before PS", color='blue', alpha=0.6)
        ax.bar(x + 0.2, after_values, width=0.4, label="After PS", color='orange', alpha=0.6)

        ax.set_title(metric)
        ax.set_xticks(x)
        ax.set_xticklabels(sensitive_attrs, rotation=45, ha="right")
        ax.legend()

    fig.suptitle(f"Fairness Metrics Comparison for {model_name}")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Plot for each model
plot_fairness_metrics(rf_fairness_comparison_df, "Random Forest (Full)")
plot_fairness_metrics(ab_fairness_comparison_df, "AdaBoost (Full)")
plot_fairness_metrics(lr_fairness_comparison_df, "Logistic Regression (Full)")
